
[1]radiant

   RA'DIANT, a. Shooting or darting rays of light; beaming with
   brightness; emitting a vivid light or splendor; as the radiant sun.

   Mark what radiant state she spreads.

   Radiant in glittering arms and beamy pride.

    RA'DIANT, n. In optics, the luminous point or object from which light
                  emanates, that falls on a mirror or lens.
